    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-11T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-11T21:00:00-05:00" n="639"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d639">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/30393: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Ciudad Juarez</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scherer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ciudad Juarez</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-11T20:00:00-06:00"
                            >August 11, 1936—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 12—12:49 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to the Embassy’s telegram August 11, noon. Nicolas Rodriquez landed at
                    Ciudad Juarez 5 p.m., was accompanied by General Juan Felipe Rico, garrison
                    commander, to International Bridge, was admitted by American immigration
                    authorities 6 o’clock. Probably will spend night in El Paso. No demonstrations.
                    Embassy informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scherer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
